<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>智能新闻| smithsonianmag.com</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/rss/smart-news/</link><description>智能新闻的 RSS 提要</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 13:26:42 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>这是水下机器人在法国最深的沉船中发现的东西，这是一艘停泊在地中海底部的 16 世纪商船</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-what-underwater-robots-are-finding-at-frances-deepest-shipwreck-a-16th-century-merchant-vessel-resting-at-the-bottom-of-the-mediterranean-180988685/</link><description>这艘船被称为“卡马拉特 4 号”，船上装载着大炮、大锅和数百件陶瓷——这些物品在海底仍然清晰可见。研究人员正在勘察该地点并仔细恢复一小部分文物</description><pubDate>Thu, 07 May 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/heres-what-underwater-robots-are-finding-at-frances-deepest-shipwreck-a-16th-century-merchant-vessel-resting-at-the-bottom-of-the-mediterranean-180988685/</guid></item><item><title>二战后，这位德国艺术家通过颠倒了他的画作，彻底颠覆了艺术世界</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-world-war-ii-this-german-artist-turned-the-art-world-upside-down-literally-by-inverting-his-paintings-180988689/</link><description>乔治·巴塞利兹 (Georg Baselitz) 是一位擅长运用透视法并在头上翻转画布的著名画家，最近去世，享年 88 岁</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 19:42:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/after-world-war-ii-this-german-artist-turned-the-art-world-upside-down-literally-by-inverting-his-paintings-180988689/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚能成为第一个消除宫颈癌的国家吗？进展顺利，但 HPV 疫苗接种率和筛查率正在下降</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-australia-be-the-first-country-to-eliminate-cervical-cancer-its-on-track-but-hpv-vaccination-and-screening-rates-are-falling-180988681/</link><description>该国于2007年实施了全国疫苗接种计划，以预防该疾病。新数据显示，2021年，没有25岁以下女性被诊断出患有宫颈癌，这是一个重要的里程碑</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 15:57:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/could-australia-be-the-first-country-to-eliminate-cervical-cancer-its-on-track-but-hpv-vaccination-and-screening-rates-are-falling-180988681/</guid></item><item><title>《蝇王》在新迷你剧中首次出现在电视上。在 20 世纪 50 年代，现在著名的小说几乎从未出版过</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-miniseries-brings-lord-of-the-flies-to-television-for-the-first-time-in-the-1950s-the-now-famous-novel-almost-never-got-published-180988684/</link><description>出版商多次拒绝《蝇王》的原稿，但这个故事至今仍引起热议。作家威廉·戈尔丁后来荣获诺贝尔文学奖</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 14:07:48 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/new-miniseries-brings-lord-of-the-flies-to-television-for-the-first-time-in-the-1950s-the-now-famous-novel-almost-never-got-published-180988684/</guid></item><item><title>鲸鱼蒂米在德国海岸搁浅数周后被释放到北海。这是正确的决定吗？</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/timmy-the-whale-was-released-into-the-sea-after-being-stranded-off-the-german-coast-for-weeks-was-that-the-right-call-180988679/</link><description>座头鲸于三月底首次进入浅水区，但过去几周其健康状况恶化。专家批评了拯救这只动物的努力，这可能弊大于利</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 13:13:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/timmy-the-whale-was-released-into-the-sea-after-being-stranded-off-the-german-coast-for-weeks-was-that-the-right-call-180988679/</guid></item><item><title>汉坦病毒的致命爆发导致大西洋上的一艘游轮搁浅。以下是关于罕见传染病的知识</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-deadly-outbreak-of-hantavirus-has-stranded-a-cruise-ship-in-the-atlantic-ocean-heres-what-to-know-about-the-rare-contagion-180988680/</link><description>与该船有关的三人已死亡，卫生官员已确认共有两例确诊病例和五例疑似感染病例。该病毒通常通过受污染的啮齿动物粪便传播</description><pubDate>Tue, 05 May 2026 21:08:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-deadly-outbreak-of-hantavirus-has-stranded-a-cruise-ship-in-the-atlantic-ocean-heres-what-to-know-about-the-rare-contagion-180988680/</guid></item><item><title>面部识